Phool Chor

"Stealing flowers is not a crime" 
"You can offer it to your God, the one you love, and it takes off the sin behind stealing"
"So if the intentions behind a theft includes the almighty, does the sin become legal?"
"No. But doing it for a loved one surely can turn a sin into virtue for we all worship a God
who believed in stealing, who believed in loving, who believed in stealing for love"


Darkness loves Darkness

"What is it about darkness that drives or scares love away?"
"Isn't the entire purpose of darkness to induce fear : into humans, into their hearts?"
"Not the life-taking, hell inducing darkness; but the one that resides in each being, in one tiny corner of their heart and mind, when they battled for light, the one that turned out to be their survival kit"
"If something helps us to survive, is it a good or bad thing?"
"What it helps us to grow into, decides the verdict"
"So if darkness loves darkness, won't the light and love save them?"
"But can darkness ever co-exist with love?"
